The paper deals with the statistical analysis of cyber attacks, which is a core topic in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a new mathematical framework for describing cyber attacks, which involves stochastic processes (cs.SI). The analysis of the honeypot dataset involves the use of statistical methods, such as time series analysis and long-range dependence, which are commonly used in network intrusion detection and cyber security (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of data analysis and modeling techniques, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
